      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense, but I think the ratio for a minor second might actually be closer to 16:15 in equal temperament? Anyway, you mentioned how the brain processes these. Could you explain the \"critical band\" concept? I've heard that the physical interference of the sound waves themselves plays a role in that \"roughness\" sensation.",
